  "title": "Sr Associate Engineer, Failure Analysis",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform TEM (transmission electron microscopy) sample preparation using Focused-ion beam/Scanning Electron Microscope for semiconductor failure analysis and characterization.</li>\n  <li>Perform pre-FIB related sample preparation such as optical microscope inspection, Si wafer navigation, chip delayering, RIE etching, sputter coating, and etc.</li>\n  <li>Participate in new failure analysis techniques development and evaluation of new technologies</li>\n  <li>Demonstrate a sense of urgency and quality mindset to support urgent and critical Fab operation requests.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Engineering (Electrical / Electronics / Mechatronics and Microelectronics Engineering)</li>\n  <li>This role requires to work in the 12hr night-shift pattern.</li>\n  <li>Fast learning and good hands-on capability</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience on FIB for TEM sample preparation is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Basic knowledge in semiconductor field</li>\n  <li>Good interpersonal and communication skills, team workers, independent and self-disciplined.</li>\n</ul>",
